Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

## Changes Made:

### 1. Installed @vercel/analytics package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` to dependencies in package.json
- Package version installed: latest from npm registry
- Updated package-lock.json with new dependency tree

### 2. Modified app/app/layout.tsx
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the body tag (after children)
- Placement follows Next.js App Router best practices for analytics

## Implementation Details:

Following the official Vercel documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart:
- This is a Next.js App Router project, so the Analytics component was added to the root layout file
- The component is placed at the end of the body tag as recommended
- No additional configuration is required; the component will automatically track page views

## Verification:

✅ Build: Successfully compiled with `npm run build`
✅ Linting: Passed with no errors using `npm run lint`
✅ TypeScript: Type checking completed successfully during build
⚠️ Tests: Pre-existing test failures unrelated to Analytics integration (missing blog content)

## Additional Notes:

- The Analytics component will only start collecting data when deployed to Vercel
- In development mode, it won't send data to Vercel servers
- No environment variables or additional configuration needed
- The integration is framework-aware and optimized for Next.js

## Files Modified:

- app/app/layout.tsx - Added Analytics import and component
- app/package.json - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- app/package-lock.json - Updated with new dependency tree
